        </p>
        <p>
          This widespread adoption addresses fundamental challenges in digital credential management. Traditional systems require ongoing maintenance and present single points of failure, while blockchain-based badges provide permanent, decentralized verification that persists regardless of organizational changes.
        </p>
        <p>
          Ultimately, this approach represents the convergence of Web2 familiarity with Web3 infrastructure advantages. Organizations gain blockchain benefits—immutability, decentralization, and cryptographic security—without the complexity typically associated with distributed systems.
